  "prompt": "What are the type of questions which belong to human behavior topic and not to human nature topic?",
  "response": "Human behavior and human nature are closely related but distinctly different concepts. Questions pertaining to human behavior generally focus on actions, reactions, and decisions made by individuals or groups in specific contexts. These questions often involve observable and measurable actions and tend to explore factors such as environment, cognitive processes, and social influences.\n\nHere are some examples of questions that belong to the human behavior topic:\n\n1. How do social media platforms influence our daily decision-making processes?\n2. What strategies can improve teamwork and collaboration in a workplace setting?\n3. How does peer pressure impact decision-making in adolescents?\n4. What are effective techniques for changing unhealthy habits?\n5. How does consumer behavior change in response to economic downturns?\n6. What factors contribute to aggressive behavior in certain situations?\n7. How do cultural differences affect communication styles in diverse teams?\n8. What role does cognitive dissonance play in attitude change?\n\nOn the other hand, human nature questions generally delve into innate characteristics, tendencies, and fundamental aspects of being human. They often pertain to traits that are considered universal or intrinsic to humanity.\n\nBy focusing on human behavior questions, one can explore how actions are shaped by external and internal influences rather than innate characteristics alone.",
